parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Genitive Masculine Singular
str2: From ek and poreuomai; to depart, be discharged, proceed, project.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
A way, road, journey, path. Apparently a primary word; a road; by implication, a progress; figuratively, a mode or means.
One. (including the neuter Hen); a primary numeral; one.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To run to. From pros and trecho; to run towards, i.e. Hasten to meet or join.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: From a compound of gonu and the alternate of pipto; to fall on the knee.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
A teacher, master. From didasko; an instructor.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To interrogate, question, demand of. From epi and erotao; to ask for, i.e. Inquire, seek.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: (a) I make, manufacture, construct, (b) I do, act, cause. Apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary; to make or do.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: To inherit, obtain (possess) by inheritance, acquire. From kleronomos; to be an heir to.
Life, both of physical (present) and of spiritual (particularly future) existence. From zao; life.
